main event: Observer sighted a moving star-like light that traveled from the N to the ESE in Jacksonville, Florida on June 26, 1969.
interesting points: The observer described the light as moving faster and being lighter than an airplane., The object was observed to have constant blinking and an erratic flight path., The sighting occurred in clear weather at approximately 9:20 PM., The observer believed the light could be a satellite based on its movement and appearance., No physical evidence or sounds were reported during the sighting.
witness description: The observer has experience and knowledge of aerial observance activities.
